    editorsNote:
      'A C2 reflection on the night of 13 April 2024, when Iran fired more than three hundred drones and missiles at Israel and gave so much advance notice that the operation behaved less like an attack than like a statement read out at length. The piece argues that the salvo worked, in its own peculiar register, only because its audience had already been trained, over years, to interpret it; and that a deterrent so dependent on shared interpretation is far more fragile than the launchers it sits on.',
